title: The Cheesiest Lines to Get a Nurse to Notice You

steps.title: Are you an appendix? Because being around you makes me want to burst.
steps.content: Are you an appendix? Because being around you makes me want to burst.

steps.title: Do you have a stethoscope? Because my heart just skipped a beat.
steps.content: Do you have a stethoscope? Because my heart just skipped a beat.

steps.title: Are you Broca’s Aphasia? Because you leave me speechless.
steps.content: Are you Broca’s Aphasia? Because you leave me speechless.

steps.title: I think I might need some Vitamin U!
steps.content: I think I might need some Vitamin U!

steps.title: You must be the cure for Alzheimer’s because you’re unforgettable.
steps.content: You must be the cure for Alzheimer’s because you’re unforgettable.

steps.title: Do you have an inhaler? Because you just took my breath away.
steps.content: Do you have an inhaler? Because you just took my breath away.

steps.title: My love for you is like diarrhea. I can’t hold it in.
steps.content: My love for you is like diarrhea. I can’t hold it in.

steps.title: Are you a pulmonary embolism? Because you make me breathless.
steps.content: Are you a pulmonary embolism? Because you make me breathless.

steps.title: Do you have a Band-Aid? I scraped my knee falling for you.
steps.content: Do you have a Band-Aid? I scraped my knee falling for you.

steps.title: Are you a defibrillator? Because you’re sending shocks right to my heart.
steps.content: Are you a defibrillator? Because you’re sending shocks right to my heart.

steps.title: I may have astigmatism, but I see clearly when I’m with you.
steps.content: I may have astigmatism, but I see clearly when I’m with you.

steps.title: You better call Life Alert because I’ve fallen for you and can’t get up.
steps.content: You better call Life Alert because I’ve fallen for you and can’t get up.

steps.title: Are you an optic chiasm? Because you’ve turned my world around.
steps.content: Are you an optic chiasm? Because you’ve turned my world around.

steps.title: You get my heart racing like an epinephrine drip.
steps.content: You get my heart racing like an epinephrine drip.

steps.title: Do you have an extra lung? Because I’ve been LUNG-ing for you.[1] X Research source
steps.content: Do you have an extra lung? Because I’ve been LUNG-ing for you. [1] X Research source

steps.title: My love for you burns stronger than a urinary tract infection.
steps.content: My love for you burns stronger than a urinary tract infection.

steps.title: I’m not an organ donor, but I’d give you my heart.
steps.content: I’m not an organ donor, but I’d give you my heart.

steps.title: If you keep being this sweet, you might give me diabetes.
steps.content: If you keep being this sweet, you might give me diabetes. [2] X Research source

steps.title: Blood is red. Cyanosis is blue. I get tachycardia when I’m with you.
steps.content: Blood is red. Cyanosis is blue. I get tachycardia when I’m with you.

steps.title: I don’t want an apple a day because I don’t want you to go away.
steps.content: I don’t want an apple a day because I don’t want you to go away. [3] X Research source

steps.title: Did you hear that? Even my heart murmurs, “I love you!”
steps.content: Did you hear that? Even my heart murmurs, “I love you!”

steps.title: You make my dopamine levels soar.
steps.content: You make my dopamine levels soar.

steps.title: Is there something in your eye? Nope. Just a sparkle.
steps.content: Is there something in your eye? Nope. Just a sparkle.

steps.title: I don’t want to get better because that would mean I’d never see you again.
steps.content: I don’t want to get better because that would mean I’d never see you again.

steps.title: I think my vestibulocochlear nerve is damaged. I keep falling for you.
steps.content: I think my vestibulocochlear nerve is damaged. I keep falling for you.

steps.title: I think you’re suffering from a lack of Vitamin Me.
steps.content: I think you’re suffering from a lack of Vitamin Me.

steps.title: Am I drowning? Because I would love some mouth-to-mouth.
steps.content: Am I drowning? Because I would love some mouth-to-mouth.

steps.title: Do I have to get critically injured to see you again, or can I have your number?
steps.content: Do I have to get critically injured to see you again, or can I have your number?

steps.title: Is it my olfactory, or do you smell really good?
steps.content: Is it my olfactory, or do you smell really good? [4] X Research source

steps.title: I hope you know CPR because you take my breath away.
steps.content: I hope you know CPR because you take my breath away.

steps.title: I think I have a tic because I can’t stop winking at you.
steps.content: I think I have a tic because I can’t stop winking at you.

steps.title: Does your left eye hurt? Because you’ve been looking right all day.
steps.content: Does your left eye hurt? Because you’ve been looking right all day.

steps.title: You should diagnose me to see if I’m a good partner.
steps.content: You should diagnose me to see if I’m a good partner.

steps.title: We should study anatomy together sometime.
steps.content: We should study anatomy together sometime.

steps.title: I think you should take your temperature instead. You’re looking pretty hot.
steps.content: I think you should take your temperature instead. You’re looking pretty hot.

steps.title: You’d be amazed by how fast I can do rapid clothing removal.
steps.content: You’d be amazed by how fast I can do rapid clothing removal.

steps.title: Did we go to school together? I could swear we had chemistry.
steps.content: Did we go to school together? I could swear we had chemistry.
